sectionedDescription.description:
This separate listing allows you to book the ENTIRE UPSTAIRS of LOCKE B & B. If you wish to book just one or two private rooms, or our Honeymoon Suite, please find those separate listings also on Airbnb.

ENTIRE UPSTAIRS of LOCKE B & B accommodates your group of up to 12 people. 6 private bedrooms, 2 kitchens, 2 baths, 2 verandas. Quality mattresses and linens. Historical building and town. Great for wedding parties, family reunions, hobby clubs, photo clubs, art workshops, company retreats, etcetera.

Host your group here and rent all six bedrooms and you’ll have the entire upstairs!

Martha (or a substitute host) is just a phone call away any hour for emergencies and very nearby to assist. Concierge services also available for your event for an extra fee.
Hot breakfast included for your entire group (one sitting), cooked downstairs in our commercial kitchen, delivered upstairs at 9:30 a.m. or other arranged time.

Two other great lunch/dinner restaurants are just 50 walking steps away from Locke B & B. Al the Wops for excellent steaks, cocktails and a jukebox, and the Locke Garden has excellent Chinese food. Tony’s and Wimpy’s in Walnut Grove are two more awesome nearby restaurant-bars. Lively nightlife on the weekends, especially!

Parking on Main Street is first come, first serve and can get especially busy on the weekends.  There is also a public parking lot at the north entrance to the town. Drop off your guest(s) and their bags, then find a parking spot.
If you arrive in your boat, tie it up at the public dock in Walnut Grove, (or sometimes at Locke Boathouse) or tie it up to the trees in Railroad Cut, right behind the town, and arrange with us for help carrying your bags to Locke B & B.

QUIET ZONE is in the wood walkway and back entrance area of the exterior of our building at ALL hours, day and night, PLEASE, so not to disturb our very nearby neighbors who are used to a very quiet atmosphere! Whisper level only, please. Courteous “quietude” encouraged in the interior hallway as well when fellow guests might be sleeping in their rooms. Some guests like to sleep during the day. Thank you!

reviews.comments: Great house and host! Would stay here again!

Nice big house for a family gathering at Thanksgiving! Loved cooking in the large well-stocked kitchen. I was so appreciative that our three dogs were welcomed. Hot water was very slow, so first shower was cold. Spa and pool were full of leaves and spa never got up to temperature, (you have to text host to turn on). Overall, we had great experience. Robyn was so helpful.

Robyn was an amazing host! The house was beautiful and very welcoming. I enjoyed my gateway stay. Robyn responded quickly and offered options. Robyn was warm and generous. I adored her. I recommended you this place :-) ❤️❤️❤️❤️❤️
Great communication with the host. Good location if you want to be in S. Sacramento - easy to get to. Lots of room.

Perfect spot for friends to gather and relax by the river! We spent all day Saturday on the river, and all day Sunday by the pool. Robyn was incredibly helpful and responsive the entire time, and the house was great. Huge kitchen for us all to gather and cook in, all around the central island. The pool was so much fun and so was the hot tub. Comfy rooms and spaces to kick back. Everyone loved it.

A large, comfortable house.  If you're planning to use the pool you should expect to pay the $250 to heat it. Water temp was 66 degrees when we arrived and too cold to enjoy.  After heating it was great and we spent lots of time in it!  Heating the spa is included in the rental fee.  As previously stated Robyn is great at communicating with renters.

Our family had a wonderful mini vacation at Robyn’s house. The house is beautiful, there is plenty of room to relax in, very large kitchen for preparing meals, and a very quiet neighborhood. Robyn was an excellent host and responded immediately to any requests that we had. It was a pleasure dealing with her.

Robyn’s home was the perfect spot for gathering a large, multigenerational family together. We loved everything about the house. The backyard is OUTSTANDING. The pool and spa are exceptional. We loved being outdoors with so many different spots to gather. The house also has an upstairs family room as well as the huge living room downstairs. Great location with the 5 Freeway just minutes away. The levee biking and walking trail is out the back gate.

This place is gorgeous! We absolutely loved our stay. The location was perfect, the pool and spa were the highlight of our kids’ time. Robyn quickly responded whenever we had a question or problem and they were resolved in a timely manner.
We had a great couple of days in Sacramento. The house was beautiful, host was responsive and they had everything we needed. The hot tub was so worth it! We would definitely stay here again.

Maria’s place was great and super clean which we really appreciated which means we could wind down and relax asap. Maria was very responsive and helpful when we communicated with her. She has a lovely home and wonderful garden with lots of fruits and vegetables!

reviews.response:
Thank you, Kelly, for your sweet words! I wanted to clarify that the spa is being heated by electrical power, up to 107 degrees if needed.
Kelly is a new mother that brought her baby and elderly frail parents with her for this brief two night stay. Unfortunately, her exhaustion and anxiety got the best of her. She failed to read the listing description, check in instructions and the House Manual that is prominently displayed in the kitchen area. By answering her numerous unnecessary questions at all hours of day and night (both nights), I believe I showed her human understanding and compassion that will lead her to become a better short term rental guest in the future😊.

reviews.comments: Great place to stay!  Maria was an incredible host. We will absolutely be back.

Our family stayed here for over a month and it was very comfortable and spacious! It felt like home. The covered porch and fireplace along with the pool, hot tub and grill/outdoor kitchen were so great! We really enjoyed our stay here! Great location! We will definitely be coming back if we have the opportunity!

Beautiful home and location! Felt like we were at home away from home with the well stocked kitchen and bathrooms. I cooked several meals and there were so many essential tools and supplies already available which was incredible. The house is super cozy we immediately felt so comfortable. We enjoyed sitting in the stunning backyard in the mornings. So many games and activities as well. Truly a wonderful experience!
Amazing home, felt right at home. The host was very helpful and friendly.

Enjoyed our stay! Maria the host was very communicative. The home was comfortable and there were no issues. We loved how easy it was to meet the checkout list - simple and nothing too onerous. Supplies were well stocked and better than most other airbnb's we've stayed at (e.g., kitchenware, kitchen supplies, extra bathroom supplies, lots of towels, etc). Five stars for both Maria and this home.

This home is everything and MORE!  Absolutely beautiful from the inside out!  It also feels so warm and cozy and like your home away from home!  They had everything and more that you might need for your stay!  We traveled with kiddos and the house with the corn hole and horse shoes plus pool and hot tub was wonderful and keep our boys busy the entire time!  There’s an amazing kids room with toys and books that became our little guys favorite place to be!  More than enough space inside the home and the outdoor seating areas with the fireplace and the outdoor kitchen was just perfect to sit and enjoy and cook while we watch the kids play!  Their garden is spectacular and a beautiful place to look at as well - respectfully admiring the hard work that had to go into creating that beautiful space!  From beginning to end this was our best and favorite Airbnb experience. Maria was fantastic!  We booked pretty last minute and she was responsive and answered all the questions we had. We explained our trip with added dinner party guests and Maria was fantastic and supportive and helped us get that situated as well!  She was also thoughtful on setting up the pool safety gate knowing that we had some younger kids running around as well!  Working with Maria made this experience easy and took away a lot of the stress and worry so that we could just enjoy our trip!  No question we will absolutely stay here again and not only this property but the others they own as well!  Highly recommend this home and Maria for all your stays in Roseville and the Sacramento area!!  Can’t say enough about how truly fantastic this experience was!  Thank you Maria for everything!!

Maria’s home was fantastic! We appreciated everything from the master retreat all the way to the blankets for outdoor lounging and pool toys. We especially loved all the little details, such as the fall decor and goodies waiting for us when we arrived. We would absolutely stay here again and highly recommend Maria’s beautiful home!
Wonderful experience from start to finish!!
Maria is awesome. The facilities and price paid was well worth it.

sectionedDescription.description:
Beautiful, 4bdrm/3bath, luxury Tuscan villa with a solar heated pool (swimming May through September), spa, hot outdoor shower, California room with gas log fireplace and a gorgeous built-in outdoor kitchen. Tesla charger and a piano! Cook at home in a fully stocked gourmet kitchen or take a 5 min drive to nearby family and high end restaurants, movie theaters, and shopping. 
1.5 hours to Tahoe, San Francisco or Napa, and much more, please see Host Guidebook.

This 3,000 sqft one level all fenced Tuscany villa is located on a safe quiet street with a green belt across the street and a short walk to the neighborhood park and playground. Whole house is lovingly set up for the needs of all your family members. This house is very specious and has multiple sitting areas for conversations and dining inside and outside. Play in the spa and pool or venture out and rent motorized as well as non-motorized sports at Folsom Lake. Pool swimming weather is approximately May through September, depending on the weather). Sacramento Aquatic center also provides non-motorized water sport rentals. Paddleboarding or kayaking anyone? 
Multiple wineries and craft breweries to visit and explore. Kids' activities include Sunsplash Water Park, Quarry Park Adverntures, bowling, mini golf, bumper cars to name a few, please see Host Guidebook for more activities and places to eat. 
Guest satisfaction and happiness are our number one priority. We own and operate two houses as short-term rentals and take a lot of pride in it. Both houses are within a mile from each other, and we live nearby also. We are in the process of remodeling a large lakefront house with a pool in Clearlake with amazing views. Be on a look out for that listing!
We are always available to assist our guests with any questions or concerns. Please let us know sooner rather than later that way we can make your stay more enjoyable, and the house will be ready for the next guest. But, most importantly, have a wonderful time and build those lifetime memories with your family and friends!

Entire home

During your stay please msg through AirBnb if you have any questions/concerns. Thank you!

Layback quiet family neighborhood. Nature trails area is right across the street. 5-10 min to major shopping and restaurants. 25 min to downtown Sacramento. 30 min to SMF international airport. 
1 hour to the nearest ski resort. 1.5 hours to Lake Tahoe skiing and hiking. So is the city of San Francisco and the famous wine region of Napa Valley.

If you are not renting a car, Uber/Lift will be your best friend. 
At least 5 parking spots available at the house: two inside the garage and three in the driveway. Street parking is also permitted.

Since it is a quiet residential neighborhood, please no parties, noise level should be down from 10 pm to 8 am.
Absolutely no smoking in the house, $500 fine enforced.
Side yard orchard and vegetable garden is reserved for the owners, but we share:) Feel free to take a stroll and admire.
Your lovely pets are welcome to come for a $500 refundable deposit.

Beautiful Spanish Style Oasis located in the heart of The Sacramento Delta.  Minutes away from the Lodi Wine Country.  Families or couples can enjoy the luxury of home style vacationing minutes from the Sacramento River!!  

Beautifully restored 1928 Spanish style home tucked into a quiet residential street on an island in the Sacramento Delta region and only 600 feet from the Sacramento River. Lush landscaping with a tropical theme. Courtyard for breakfast, dinner or cocktails. Two bedrooms with one bedroom providing adjoining reading room with views of beautiful palm filled backyard. New kitchen with all amenities. One tub/shower bathroom newly designed. Small fishing ,boating and agricultural community. Several restaurants and shops in town right across the bridge. Within fifteen minutes driving time, you can access over 40 wineries representing the Lodi wine appellation. Wine tours and tastings are available every day and year round. 40 minutes to downtown Sacramento, 1 hour and fifteen minutes to San Francisco, one hour to famous Gold Country where gold was discovered in1849. Yes you can pan for Gold!! This home is immaculately clean and maintained. Absolutley charming!!! Come stay at " Casa Mira Lago" !!!

The other two bedrooms worked out great for our adult children. The fenced backyard and covered patio was nice; it was a great space to sit and watch our dogs run around.
Location of the house was close to shopping, restaurants, parks, and freeways; and it was centrally located, so it was convenient for getting to our family events in the Sacramento delta, Natomas, and Placer County.
We really enjoyed our stay, and felt at home. Venci was a great host; and was quite responsive when I had questions.
Enjoyed our recent stay around Graduation/Memorial Day as it was centrally located to the major events we were attending in Sacramento. It felt like home and everything was stressfree!!

I needed a night to stay on a long road trip & this home was perfect. Comfortable, clean space - beautiful kitchen. Garage access made it easy to get myself & my 2 small dogs unloaded late at night.
Venci was quick to respond, great instructions & the home was beautiful!
As a heads up only if you do have dogs, the neighbors behind & on the side of the home have dogs. They were very loud, barking & chasing the fences when I would try to let my dogs. Thank you for a wonderful stay.

Great place to stay calm neighborhood house had all amenities you need. Would definitely stay here again if we return to Sacramento!

reviews.comments: We could not have asked for anything more from this house and host! Our family of six came to my hometown of Sacramento for a special family event and this accommodation allowed us to spend quality time together relaxing in the pool, sitting in the beautiful backyard and taking walks in nature in nearby  Ancil Hoffman park. The house is fantastic with modern yet comfortable furnishings. If we need to return to Sacramento again I would love to stay here again. Stu was a great host, checking in to make sure all was well. We would give this stay more than 5 stars if we could!

We've had a wonderful time staying at Stuart's house! There's plenty of space for a family to get together, as well as have their privacy, and everything is just so smartly designed and optimized for fun and relaxation. With a pool deep enough to have a diving board, located next to a small putting green and boards for bean bag toss, your cranky teen may just feel like a small kid again, while the grandpa can relax in the plentiful shade of the covered patio, several umbrellas, and the trees around the backyard. Pool chairs, towels, sunscreen - everything is within reach. The kitchen is stocked with any and all utensils you may possibly need, and even fresh coffee beans in the grinder. There's plenty of options for family entertainment, from children’s books to board games and home theater projector, as well as fast internet connection. What stood out for us was how Stuart's house combines all the smart tech with the warm atmosphere, which made our stay so pleasant and memorable.

Our stay at Stuart’s place was amazing!!! The house felt like home and we enjoyed spending family time together. The yard is spectacular and the pool was great. We loved being there and would book again when in the area. I highly recommend this home especially for families, it’s spacious and well designed to meet everyone’s needs. We had a great time!
Georgina
reviews.response: Thank you Georgina! Glad everyone had a wonderful time. And thank you for taking such excellent care of our home. Much appreciated.

reviews.comments: This place was beautiful through and through and sooooo kid friendly.

reviews.comments: Jennifer is a responsive, good and caring host. The property and neighborhood are very old and the home and decor are somewhat quirky, but the home was clean and met our needs and we enjoyed our stay. I recommend guests pay close attention to Jennifer’s detailed instructions regarding the heating/AC and swamp cooler as it is a much different set up than most places and you will want to be sure you adjust it correctly to meet your needs. This home is professionally cleaned with fresh linens and towels.  1500 sf. of luxury.  There is a tv in every room and patio area with access to Netflix, Amazon Prime, Hulu ext.  Our beautiful kitchen is fully stocked for all of your cooking needs.  Beds in each room are either memory foam or have a memory foam topper with waterproof mattress protector for extra cleanliness. Quiet older neighborhood.  Lots of trees.  Good neighborhood.

There is driveway parking and free street parking.

Welcome home! 

Come and relax in this cozy home away from home. High vaulted ceiling and freshly floor updated with luxury vinyl plank. Lots of natural light. AC & heater controlled using a smart Nest thermostat. 

--- KITCHEN & LIVING ROOM ---
Enjoy home cooked meals w/a fully stocked kitchen with a BBQ grill in the backyard as well. There are washer and dryer in the unit and 2 side-by-side parking spaces in the driveway. High speed internet with Fire TV. 

--- BACKYARD ---
The Sacramento area is famous for its Delta breeze. On a nice day, enjoy our backyard with outdoor sofa. Perfect for family fun and tea time.

--- WORK FROM HOME ---
There is an office desk, chair, and a 23'' monitor in the master bedroom. 

--- LOCATION ---
This house is ideal for family stay, traveling professionals, and corporate business trips. This house is located in a safe and family oriented neighborhood. Only minutes' drive to all 3 medical facilities on Laguna Blvd, 10 minutes to Apple campus. 

District 56, Walmart, Costco, restaurants, and coffee shops are just blocks away. Message me for recommendations on where to eat. Elk Grove has so many good restaurants!

Kids love the playground and parks in Elk Grove. If you travel with kids, be sure to bring them to a few nearby.

There is a hiking trail nearby just behind Oneto park.


--- OTHERS ---
The sprinkler activates at 1am at night for about half an hour. So please be careful if you come home late at night, stay dry! =)

We have a Ring alarm system. It's off by default. But if you want extra peace of mind and want to use it. Feel free to connect with me after check in for instructions.


--- PET POLICY ---
We are dog friendly. I love cats as well but unfortunately I'm very allergic, and cannot host your kitten friends. 

As a former dog mom, I understand the importance of bringing your furry buddy on your trip, but please also know that pets come with extra cleaning. We will charge an additional $100 for cleaning to ensure the space is clean for the next guests and for your return in the future.

Only 1 small or medium dog is allowed in the house (under 25lbs)

* Breed restriction: German shepherds, Pit bull terriers, Cane corsos, Rottweilers, Staffordshire terriers, Akitas, Mastiffs, Great Danes, Doberman pinschers


--- SMOKE & DRUG ----
No smoking/vape/e-cig/candles. You will be charge $200 for additional cleaning to remove odor and replace filter.

No drug use in the house.
